## 2026-03-27 - parseInlineValue for boolean type accepts any non-"false" string as true
- Changed boolean branch to only accept "true"/"false" (case-insensitive) and return `null` for any other value.
- `handleCreate` and `handleCreateAndNew` now validate the parsed value before submitting, calling `setCreateError` with a descriptive message if `null` (i.e. invalid boolean string).
