## 2026-03-27 - Scroll position resets on search — applying or clearing a search filter jumps virtual scroll to top instead of preserving the user's position
- Added scroll anchor preservation: before any filter change (searchQuery, typeFilter, refFilter), the first visible item path is saved in `scrollAnchorPathRef`. After `flatItems` changes due to the filter, a `useLayoutEffect` scrolls to that item in the new list. If the anchor item isn't in the filtered results, scroll to top.
- Used mutable refs (`virtualScrollTopRef`, `flatItemsRef`, `itemOffsetsRef`) synced every render to avoid stale closure issues in filter callbacks (which have empty deps arrays). Pattern: sync refs with `ref.current = value` immediately after useMemo in render body.
- Added `isFilterChangeRef` boolean to gate the restoration layoutEffect so it only fires on filter changes, not on token data updates.

